BIRNIN-KEBBI – Following the situation of the country and Sallah celebrations ahead, the Kebbi state command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) on Friday announced the deployments of 650 of her personnel to beef up security during and after Sallah celebrations in Kebbi. The deployments were contained in a press release signed by the command’s image maker DSC Hakeem Babatunde Adeyemi, according to him, the personnel were drawn from different units which also include plain cloth officers. He explained that the massive deployments cover worship centres and recreational areas and guard valuable government assets and other public facilities “aside from the stationed officers another contingent of armed NSCDC personnel will monitor everything, therefore we are working in synergy with other sister security outfits in Kebbi state”. While urging the civil populace to report any suspicious or unusual movement he extends a Sallah message to all Muslims across the country from the new state commandant Kebbi NSCDC Abdullahi Salihu Ebbo who he said also assured people of Kebbi state a peaceful Sallah festivities and a renewed commitment to flush out criminal elements in the state.